  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "As it stands now, helm makes a .helm folder in the home directory. \r\n```\r\n.helm/\r\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Helm.config\r\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 patches\r\n\r\n1 directory, 1 file\r\n```\r\n\r\n[XDG standards](https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html) specify that config files should go in ~/.config and data in ~/.local/share. \r\n\r\nThe entirety of ~/.helm should be moved to ~/.local/share/helm, because it contains application data and Helm.config really doesn't seem to be much of a config file, containing only a version number and data used to determine if the user should be asked for payment.\r\n\r\nGreat work guys, keep it up.",
